Young swordmasters Mia and the ever-masked
Marth. What destiny does summer hold for the
two of them? They appear in Fire Emblem:
Radiant Dawn / Awakening.

A member of the Greil Mercenaries known
for his gentle demeanor. He's taking to the
battlefield in a swimsuit this time. Appears
in Fire Emblem: Radiant Dawn.

One of the Grado Empire's six generals, known
as the Fluorspar. Her loyalty is unwavering, even
under the summer sea's waves. Appears in Fire
Emblem: The Sacred Stones.

A young mage of Renais possessed of a rather
unusual temperament. She is searching for signs
of new magics among the summer sands.
Appears in Fire Emblem: The Sacred Stones.

A mercenary with a love for gambling. He's in
the tropics hoping luck's tide turns in his favor.
Appears in Fire Emblem: The Sacred Stones.

Units on the opposing team with Range = 2
cannot move through a space adjacent to the
holder of this seal. (Does not affect units with
Pass.) When foe with this seal is defeated,
restores 10 HP to unit that defeated foe and
inflicts Special cooldown count+1 on that unit
after combat.
